# @param {Integer[]} nums
# @return {Integer}
def missing_integer(nums)
  # Sort the nums array to ensure sequential order
  nums.sort!
  
  # Initialize sum with the first element, assuming the single element prefix is sequential
  sum = nums[0]
  
  # Iterate through nums to find the longest sequential prefix
  (1...nums.length).each do |i|
    # If the current element is the next sequential number, add it to sum
    if nums[i] == nums[i - 1] + 1
      sum += nums[i]
    else
      # If the sequence breaks, exit the loop
      break
    end
  end
  
  # Find the smallest missing integer greater than or equal to the sum
  missing = sum
  while nums.include?(missing)
    missing += 1
  end
  
  missing
end
